## Page Organization

### File Structure
```
pages/
  PageName/
    index.jsx          # Main page component
    components/        # Page-specific components (optional)
      Component1.jsx
      Component2.jsx
```

### Component Extraction
- Extract reusable components to `src/components/`
- Extract page-specific components to `pages/PageName/components/`
- Keep page files focused and readable

## Lazy Loading

### Page Import
```javascript
// In navigation/index.jsx
const PageName = lazy(() => import('@/pages/PageName'));

// Page must have default export
export default PageName;
```

## Page Types

### Protected Pages
- Require authentication
- Use `DashboardLayout`
- Access user session from Redux

### Public Pages
- No authentication required
- Custom layout (usually centered)
- Examples: Login, Signup, NotFound

## Best Practices

### DO
- Use consistent page structure
- Handle loading and error states
- Use DashboardLayout for protected pages
- Extract complex logic into hooks
- Keep pages focused and readable

### DON'T
- Don't put business logic directly in pages
- Don't forget loading states
- Don't skip error handling
- Don't create deeply nested components in page files

